@startuml
title Medplum Delivery, Runtime Health, and Operations Lifecycle
left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor "Engineer" as engineer
component "npm workspaces\nTurborepo" as workspace
component "TypeScript builds\nserver and app artifacts" as build
component "Docker buildx" as buildx
artifact "Server image\nNode hardened base\nlinux/amd64 + linux/arm64" as serverimage
artifact "App image\nnon-root Nginx\nstatic React assets" as appimage
artifact "Image provenance + SBOM\nbuild attestations" as attestations
component "Deployment automation\nECS task-definition revision\nor Helm release" as deploy
component "Runtime health endpoint\n/healthcheck" as health
component "OpenTelemetry\nserver instrumentation" as otel
cloud "Metrics collector /\nobservability backend" as observability
database "PostgreSQL" as postgres
database "Redis" as redis

engineer --> workspace : npm ci, build, test commands
workspace --> build : build package artifacts
build --> buildx : package container inputs
buildx --> serverimage
buildx --> appimage
buildx --> attestations
serverimage --> deploy
appimage --> deploy
deploy --> health : start / replace runtime instances
health --> postgres : verifies dependency readiness\nin local server healthcheck
health --> redis : verifies dependency readiness\nin local server healthcheck
deploy --> otel : runtime emits service telemetry
otel --> observability

note bottom of buildx
The image build scripts request provenance and SBOM attestations.
Those attestations support supply-chain evidence but do not replace
deployment approval, vulnerability management, or runtime monitoring.
end note

note bottom of deploy
ECS deployment script pins services to an immutable image digest.
Helm supports version-pinned releases and waits for readiness.
end note
@enduml